6.00	Vernon_Grant	Vernon Grant	Vernon Ethelbert Grant (February 14, 1935 - July 23, 2006) was a cartoonist who did graphic novels, and is also known for his digest-sized comic book series, The Love Rangers. Usually referred to as Vern Grant, he is often credited as the person who first introduced the visual approach and concepts of Japanese manga into English-language cartooning.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Grant08library.jpg/226px-Grant08library.jpg
